HEADWORD: Spiraeic
<hw>Spi*rae"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or derived from, the meadowsweet
(<gen>Spiraea</gen>); formerly, designating an acid which is now called
<xex>salicylic acid</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spiral</ent>⟦br⟧
